Installation Tutorial

GraphQL

*API
1-Go to pickbazar->api->graphql
2-Install npm packages using 'yarn'
3-Run the graphql API using 'yarn start:dev'

*Shop
1-Go to pickbazar->shop
2-Copy tsconfig.graphql.json to tsconfig.json
3-Copy .env.template to .env
4-Update NEXT_PUBLIC_GRAPHQL_API_ENDPOINT and FRAMEWORK PROVIDER to graphql and other configuration
5-Go to root folder
6-Install all the packages using yarn
7-Run shop using yarn dev:shop-gql

*Admin
1-Go to pickbazar->admin
2-Copy .env.template to .env
3-Update NEXT_PUBLIC_GRAPHQL_API_ENDPOINT and other configuration
4-Go to root folder
5-Install all the packages using yarn
6-Run shop using yarn dev:admin-gql



REST API

*API
1-Go to pickbazar->api->rest->src->main.ts
2->Change 'const PORT = process.env.PORT || 5000' to 'const PORT = process.env.PORT || 5001'
3-Back to pickbazar->api->rest
2-Install npm packages using yarn
3-Run the graphql API using yarn start:dev

*Shop
1-Go to pickbazar->shop
2-Copy tsconfig.rest.json to tsconfig.json
3-Copy .env.template to .env
4-Update NEXT_PUBLIC_REST_API_ENDPOINT and FRAMEWORK PROVIDER to rest and other configuration
5-Go to root fold
6-Install all the packages using yarn
7-Run shop using yarn dev:shop-rest

*Admin
1-Go to pickbazar->admin->rest
2-Copy.env.template to .env
3-Update NEXT_PUBLIC_REST_API_ENDPOINT and other configuration
4-Go to root folder
5-Install all the packages using yarn
6-Run shop using yarn dev:admin-rest




